name: Walk for Warmth
ev_desc: The location for this year?s Walk for Warmth has been changed to Great Lakes. This event, sponsored by the Oakland Livingston Human Service Agency raises funds for emergency utility assistance for those in need. In the past we have had a team of “Holy Strollers” participating. You may sign-up Sundays at worship or call the church office. If you cannot walk in the event please support someone who is.

name: Ash Wednesday Service
ev_desc: Lent is a special time of the church year that calls us to focus on the quality of the life of our faith. It asks us to not just to „give something up? but add something to our life that will help us spiritually grow. Our Ash Wednesday service will include the imposition of ashes as a sign of our willingness to turn away from things that draw us from God, and toward those things that will draw us closer to God. Holy Communion will also be celebrated. See inside this newsletter for more opportunities to grow this Lenten Season.

name: Men of Grace
ev_desc: Leading us in worship on this Sunday will be the Men of Grace, a musical and witnessing ministry of Grace Gospel Fellowship in Pontiac. This musical ministry is made up of men who have completed one year of rehabilitation program at the Grace Centers of Hope and testify to the power of God to change lives. Their musical style is gospel-blues jazz with emphasis on vocal harmony. Musical selections will include spiritual, traditional and contemporary expressions. Invite family and friends and join us for this special time of worship and praise.

name: Worship Service - Graduate Recognition
ev_desc:
During the worship service we will recognize our high school and college graduates
congratulating them on their accomplishment, and asking God’s blessings on them as they plan future endeavors. A list of graduates that we have received is included in this newsletter. If you are not listed or know of someone, please contact the church office. Also, we request that graduates contact the church office to let us know if you will be present for worship this day.

name: Semi-Annual Meeting
ev_desc: All confirmed members of the congregation are requested to remain at the church for the congregational meeting following the worship service this day. We will be electing or reelecting three members to our congregational council. Those who have an interest in serving on council should contact pastor or council president, Gerry Cleasby. The election will be the main item on the agenda. A mission and financial update will also be presented.

name: Rally Day
ev_desc: The fall season gets underway with many of our activities resuming this month. We invite everyone to rally at the church this second Sunday of September for worship and a church picnic to follow. This year the picnic will be held on church grounds with food, games and fun planned for everyone, including a bounce house for kids. See inside this newsletter for more details. Join us for this time of fun and fellowship and getting the fall season kicked off to a great start. Feel free to wear picnic type clothes to church on this day!

name: Faith & Politics with Light Supper Provided
Service of Lessons and Carols
ev_desc: The Chancel Choir will help inspire our Christmas preparations with this service filled with beautiful anthems, familiar carols, and Scripture readings. It is a service that tells the story of Christmas through both word and song. Invite your family and friends to join us for this meaningful service at our regular worship time, 10:00am

name: Sunday School Christmas Program
ev_desc:
“The Wisdom of the Pine”

The children of the church will be sharing the Christmas message at this service at 10:00am. In their own unique way the Christmas story will be told. Again, invite family and friends to come and share in this program. Watch for a rehearsal schedule to be announced.

name: Christmas Service
ev_desc: Join us to proclaim the joyous news of the birth of our Lord at one of our candlelight services. Each of these services will be filled with the joyous carols of Christmas, anthems by our choirs, holy communion, and the Christmas story according to St. Luke. At the 7:00pm service a Christmas message will be added for the children. Each service ends in the traditional candle lighting ceremony as the congregation sings “Silent Night.” Oh, come, let us adore him, Christ, the Lord!

All Saints Sunday
ev_desc:
On this Sunday we remember the saints who have gone before us who have faithfully served
our Lord, and celebrate those living saints who continue to share in the work of God’s
church. Names of members who have died since the last All Saints Day will be added to our
All Saints Banner. In our prayers we invite you to share the names of loved ones that you
would like to remember. Join us this day as part of God’s great communion of saints.

name: Youth Worship Service
ev_desc:
Gather with us on this Sunday as our young people will lead us in worship. A message of
“thanksgiving” will be shared in Scripture readings, various skits, as well as music and song.
Let’s be supportive of our youth and join them in worship, praise and thanksgiving.

name: Adult Discussion
ev_desc:
We invite all to join us for these informal
discussions that will focus on various issues of
the day. Topics will be announced a week to
two weeks prior to the meeting time. We hope
to look at various sides of an issue and see how
our faith and biblical traditions can inform our
understanding. We welcome various voices and
perspectives no matter what the issue may be.

name: Thanksgiving Eve Service
ev_desc:
The familiar Thanksgiving hymn says it all, “Now thank we all our God, with heart and
hands and voices.” Let’s not leave God out of Thanksgiving. Before you gather around your
thanksgiving table with loved ones and friends, join us Thanksgiving Eve to thank the One
from whom all blessings flow. Let’s also be mindful of those in need and fill up our food
basket this day.

name: WELCA
ev_desc:
All WOMEN are invited to the WELCA Meetings - usually the first Thursday of each month at 10:00 am. There is a short meeting followed by a Bible Study lead by Pastor Negele. At noon each attendee brings a sandwich and a dessert and beverage is provided by that month’s hostess. Also the 2nd and 4th Tuesdays of the month at 9:00 am they gather to make quilts which are shipped to Lutheran World Relief to assist with diasters around the world.
Come and join in!

name: Early Easter Service
ev_desc: Our Lenten journey is complete. The Cross is not the final destination! Jesus is Alive! He is Risen! The journey ends with new life. Come celebrate with us at one of our joyous Easter Services. Please note the change of service times. The candles will be lighted, the flowers will be blooming, the bells will be ringing, the choir will be singing – all our senses will be celebrating this glorious day. Holy Communion will be celebrated at both services and a special Easter message for children will be shared at the 10:30am service.

name: Easter Breakfast
ev_desc: The EASTER BREAKFAST will again be part of our Easter Celebration. If you can help in any way - please indicate on your Information Slip, call the church office or Max Thompson. We will be needing donations of cut-up fresh fruit, coffee cakes & breads. You can sign up on your Information Slip what you will be able to bring.

name: Easter Egg Hunt
ev_desc: We hope to have the Annual EASTER EGG HUNT for the children. But.... we need someone to put it together. If you can help with this - please call Pat Scott or the church office. Going with the hope someone will come forth, we are asking for small toys (that would fit into plastic eggs) and small wrapped candy. Plastic eggs are not needed as we have several tubs of eggs stored.

name: Graduate Sunday
ev_desc: We encourage any members who will be graduating from high school, college, or avocational school to join us for worship on this Sunday as they will be recognized for theiraccomplishments. Please contact the church office if you can be with us. Also, if you have afamily member that is graduating please let the church office know so that their name maybe included on the list of graduates. Congratulations to all and may God’s Spirit guide themin their decisions and future careers.

name: Confirmation Sunday
ev_desc: Students completing two years of confirmation instruction will be received into theconfirmed membership of the congregation on this Sunday during the worship service. Thisalso the festival of Pentecost celebrating the gift of the Spirit coming to the disciples ofJesus and forming the church. We celebrate the birth of the church as well as God’s Spiritworking in the lives of our young people who will be affirming their baptismal vows.

name: Yard Sale Take-In Begins
ev_desc:
Planning for the 2014 Yard Sale is in full swing and your help is always needed and appreciated, we have a job to fit your skills! Intake for church members will start on Sunday, June 8th and donations from the public, June 15th. Set up of tables will be the week before June 8th with Gerry Cleasby getting things down from the attic around June 2nd so please talk to him if you can assist with these jobs. We are also looking for someone to assist Don Scott with the “electronic” area outside before and during the sale. If you can help in this area, please let Gerry or Pat Scott know. Marking is planned for Monday and Wednesday mornings from 9-12 and
Tuesday and Thursday evenings from 6-8:30 pm, times may be adjusted as needed. Virla Cleasby will have a sign up sheet for cashiers on June 1st, so if you want to help out in this area, please see her. We are asking the congregation for donations of the following: masking tape, calculators (basic), poster board, new whistles, twine, empty boxes and sharpies for making. Please have these to church by June 8th so we know what we need to
purchase. A box will be there and marked with “donations for yard sale” on the box. We have instituted some parameters for pre sales this years, along with a sign up sheet for items that you may be on the look out for. More info on this will be forth coming. Our next meeting in June 18th at 6:00 pm, all are welcome and encouraged to attend. Thanks for your help and support with this endeavor. Gerry & Maggie

ev_desc: Men’s Annual Steak Fry is June 16th, 6:30 pm at Baycourt Park on Andersonville Rd. ALL MEN ARE INVITED. Those with last names beginning with A-M please bring a salad N -Z a dessert. Be sure to sign up so there will be enough for all. A fee will be collected that evening to cover the expenses.

name: Free Movie Night \Heaven is for Real\""
CROP WALK
ev_desc: Waterford Area Crop Walk Sunday, Oct. 5th Registration: 1:30pm  Walk: 2:00pm This year’s Crop Walk for Hunger hopes toraise $20,000 within our community. Four local food agencies as well as efforts around the world will benefit from this walk. The names of those walking are posted on the wall in the fellowship area. Please support them. Sponsor forms are still available for those who would like to walk. Several routes may be walked: 5.5 mile, 3.5 mile, 1 mile, and a rocking chair. Let’s all help in combating hunger in our community and in the world. Contact Pastor or Norm Kingston for mmoreinformation.

name: Communion Worship Service - WELCA SUNDAY
ev_desc: On this special Sunday the women of the church serve as the worship servants.  ALSO - the quilts which have been constructed through the year for Lutheran World Relief will be displayed in the sanctuary for all to admire. Thank you ladies for all you do! Incidently - ALL women of Christ Lutheran are members of WELCA - notj ust those to attend the monthly meetings which we wish more would become involved.

name: 70th Anniversary Worship Service
ev_desc: All are welcome to join us to celebrate 70 years of ministry in Waterford Township. This Sunday is also Reformation Sunday for which the color of the day is red, symbolizing thefire of the Holy Spirit working within the church, and inspiring Martin Luther, back in 1517, to initiate reform within God’s church. We invite you to wear something red to symbolize that that same Spirit has worked through this congregation for 70 years and continues toinspire us to engage in God’s work. A variety of historical displays will be in the fellowshiparea, and various historical pictures will be viewed on the video screen. Be sure to indicate whether you will be able to join us for the luncheon following theservice in the lower level. Sign-up on the bulletin information slip on Sundays, or call thechurch office.  At the luncheon we will be sharing memories, giving thanks for God’sblessings, and enjoying  fellowship with one another. We also invite you to offer a special 70th Anniversary Gift to our Elevator Fund. SpecialAnniversary envelopes will be prepared for you to use. We invite you to give a multiple ofseven, ( $7, $70, or $700), or whatever you can. Join us in giving thanks for 70 years.

ev_desc: The 70th Anniversary Celebration Luncheonis Sunday, October 26 at Christ Lutheran after the worship service.
